Identify CRM Analytics Platform User Types

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.

The CRM Analytics Growth license includes the permissions that enable users to import, work with, and explore data using the CRM Analytics platform. To set up CRM Analytics, think through the different ways people access features and categorize them into user types.

Most people fall into two categories:

Users who view CRM Analytics dashboards and occasionally import data.
Administrators or managers who create apps, dashboards, lenses, and datasets, edit data, and customize the experience.

When setting up CRM Analytics, creating two basic permission sets can meet most needs: a "view" permission set for users and a "manage" permission set for administrators. You can define other user types and permissions based on your organization's needs.

We focus on users and administrators in our setup instructions.
